Title: ongoing by Tim Bray · Modern Mono
Description:
I’ve just finished setting up a new Mac (14" MBP, M2 Pro, 32G, 4T). It dawned on me that most of my really intense
    interactions with this thing involve looking at “monospace” (i.e. fixed-width) text; in Emacs where I write this blog, in
    my IDE, and in my terminal.  The ones that came with the machine by default are, well, OK, but maybe we can do better.  So I got
    on Mastodon and 
    asked: “Dear LazyWeb: Setting up a new Mac, what are some
    groovy new monospace fonts for terminals and IDEs?”
